					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Disloyalty Cards</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-01-09T18:20:57+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">January 9, 2014 1:20 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">January 9, 2014 1:20 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Marketing</b></p>
<ul>
<li>A half-dozen independent Washington, D.C. coffee shops <a href="//eater.com/archives/2014/01/06/dcs-indie-coffee-shops-team-up-for-disloyalty-card.php">are joining forces</a> to encourage ârampant disloyalty.â</li>
<li>This may be the <a href="//boingboing.net/2014/01/08/the-best-business-card-in-the.html">best business card</a> in the world.</li>
<li>Consumer emails from 1-800 Flowers and Expedia were among the <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3024574/fast-feed/the-emails-lists-we-unsubscribed-from-in-2013-1-800-flowers-expedia-party-city">most unsubscribed</a> last year.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Retail</b></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Macy&#8217;s posted <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/08/us-macys-jobs-idUSBREA071HF20140108?">strong holiday</a> season sales and gave an upbeat outlook for 2014.</li>
<li>These four apps <a href="//www.smallbizdaily.com/14809/4-apps-will-boost-new-restaurant-marketing/">can improve</a> a new restaurant&#8217;s marketing.</li>
<li>Mall <a href="//www.calculatedriskblog.com/2014/01/reis-mall-vacancy-rates-decline-in-q4.html?">vacancy rates</a> declined in the fourth quarter.</li>
<li>A <a href="//foodbeast.com/2014/01/07/these-adorable-girls-will-sell-you-cookies-for-bitcoin/">lemonade and cookie</a> stand is now accepting bitcoins.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-81654"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Washington</b></p>
<ul>
<li>The government recorded a <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/01/08/us-ran-44-billion-surplus-in-december-cbo/">budget surplus</a> of $44 billion in December which brings the government&#8217;s budget deficit for the first three months of the 2014 fiscal year to $182 billion, which is $111 billion less than the first three months of fiscal 2013.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Consumer <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/01/08/consumer-debt-grows-at-slowest-pace-in-6-months/?">debt grew</a> in November at its slowest pace in six months.</li>
<li>Chief executive confidence <a href="//247wallst.com/economy/2014/01/08/ceo-confidence-on-the-rise/?">is on</a> the rise.</li>
<li>December saw the <a href="//business.time.com/2014/01/08/survey-december-saw-best-job-growth-in-a-year/">best job growth</a> in a year.</li>
<li>Â <a href="//www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/construction-and-technology-fastest-growing-sectors-in-small-business-job-growth-in-2013-239255011.html">Construction and technology</a> were the hottest sectors in 2013, according to a report, with net job growth of 22 percent and 21 percent, respectively.</li>
<li>Sales of small companies <a href="//www.bizbuysell.com/news/media_insight.html/?">jumped 49 percent</a> in 2013, with owners receiving higher prices for their businesses but buyers getting more for their buying dollar, according to BizBuySell.</li>
<li>One of the construction industryâs leading economists says that in 2014 <a href="//www.equipmentworld.com/agcs-simonson-2014-holds-more-projects-and-tame-materials-prices-but-also-continued-worry-over-the-labor-shortage/">contractors can expect</a> more projects to bid, âtameâ materials prices and an increased concern over the availability of labor and skilled workers.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Health Care</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Nearly half of Americans with employer-based coverage report that employers are taking <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/personal-finance/2014/01/08/americans-face-higher-insurance-costs-for-employer-based-care/">more from their paychecks</a> to pay for their health insurance coverage compared to last year.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Employees</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Fed up with unpaid internships, thousands of students are <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/01/08/technology/flinja-student-freelance/index.html">using a new</a> website to help them find paid freelance gigs.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Start-Up</b></p>
<ul>
<li>These are the hottest <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/230712">e-commerce businesses</a> to start in 2014.</li>
<li>A new San Francisco-area start-up is <a href="//techcrunch.com/2014/01/08/with-mydoorman-you-never-have-to-miss-a-package-delivery-again/">trying to solve</a> the everyday annoyance of missing a UPS or FedEx delivery window. Instead of returning home to find a sticky note left on your door, you can use a mobile app to schedule an evening delivery.</li>
<li>Three million people <a href="//thenextweb.com/insider/2014/01/08/3-million-people-pledged-480-million-total-kickstarter-campaigns-2013/">pledged $480 million</a> to Kickstarter campaigns in 2013.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Cash Flow</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is a <a href="//fitsmallbusiness.com/deducting-travel-entertainment-expenses-on-taxes/">guide</a> to deducting travel and entertainment expenses.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Tennessee banks <a href="//www.tennessean.com/article/20140108/BUSINESS01/301080082/TN-banks-increase-small-business-lending?n">are increasing</a> their business lending.</li>
<li>This is how a fax <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-01-07/how-a-fax-could-cost-a-minnesota-business-owner-48-million">could cost</a> a Minnesota business owner $48 million.</li>
<li>Guess what actually did <a href="//www.buzzfeed.com/lukelewis/it-finally-happened-hell-has-literally-frozen-over?">freeze over</a> this last week.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Bucking the trend, these American small businesses are taking their <a href="//money.cnn.com/gallery/smallbusiness/2014/01/08/made-in-america-china/index.html">products</a> to China and capitalizing on its burgeoning consumer market.</li>
<li>Colombia has seen a <a href="//www.eia.gov/countries/cab.cfm?fips=CO">dramatic increase</a> in oil, natural gas, and coal production in recent years after the implementation of a series of regulatory reforms.</li>
<li>A quarter of British and Canadian businesses <a href="//gigaom.com/2014/01/08/a-quarter-of-british-and-canadian-businesses-want-their-data-taken-out-of-u-s-according-to-peer1/">want their data</a> taken out of the United States, according to a new report.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Todayâs Best Read</b></p>
<ul>
<li>An investor explains why the United States is still <a href="//seekingalpha.com/article/1935201-the-u-s-is-still-the-best-place-to-invest?">the best place</a> to invest: âEconomic fundamentals in the U.S. this year are far better than in the other big advanced countries. Since the financial crisis the U.S. is well ahead of Europe and Japan in moving to normalization, with the retreat from unconventional central banking measures already under way. After two years of fiscal austerity, the budget deficit is less than half what it was in 2010 &#8212; an important point in relation to potential decline since stronger public finances are the key to the projection of power around the world. The housing market, meantime, is recovering and there are growing signs of business confidence.â</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the Marks Group, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., a consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
